article.headline: Hawaii 56, UC Riverside 46
article.story: HONOLULU -- Roderick Flemings scored 16 points to lead Hawaii to a 56-46 win Tuesday night over UC Riverside. The Rainbow Warriors (6-3) won their third consecutive game and sixth straight at home. The Highlanders (7-3) saw a three-game winning streak snapped. Petras Balocka had 12 points and nine rebounds and Adhar Mayen scored 10 points for Hawaii. Both teams struggled offensively. Hawaii shot 38 percent from the field, but made up for it by sinking 27 of 33 free throw attempts. UC Riverside shot a season-worst 28 percent from the field, going just 1-for-12 from 3-point range. Hawaii endured a scoreless drought of four minutes and 28 seconds in the first half, but scored the final four points to take a 25-20 lead into halftime.
